# **🧠 Conceptual Summary**

TimeEngine constructs a **geometry of time** from real collider data.

- Observers define metrics  
- Metrics define distances  
- Distances define time  
- Time defines curvature  
- Curvature defines horizons  
- Horizons define the boundary of agreement between observers  

This is a **living manifold**, not a static dataset.

